---
import Layout from '~/layouts/PageLayout.astro';
import Hero from '~/components/widgets/Hero.astro';
import Content from '~/components/widgets/Content.astro';
import CallToAction from '~/components/widgets/CallToAction.astro';

const metadata = {
  title: 'Needs to Raise Money - CXO Atlas',
  description: 'Funding for growth and scaling operations. Get practical guidance for entrepreneurs seeking investment capital.',
  keywords: 'fundraising, investment, venture capital, startup funding, business growth, scaling',
  canonical: 'https://cxo-atlas.com/article/needs-to-raise-money'
};
---

<Layout metadata={metadata}>
  <Hero
    title="Needs to Raise Money"
    subtitle="Funding for growth and scaling operations. Get practical guidance for entrepreneurs seeking investment capital."
    actions={[
      { text: 'Browse All Articles', href: '/article', variant: 'primary' },
      { text: 'Back to Journey Map', href: '/#journey' },
    ]}
    image={{ src: '~/assets/images/hero-image.png', alt: 'Needs to Raise Money' }}
  />

  <Content
    id="funding-content"
    class="py-16 md:py-24"
    background="light"
  >
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <div class="prose prose-lg dark:prose-invert max-w-none">
        <h2>Stage 6: Needs to Raise Money</h2>
        
        <p>You've proven your business model works, but you need capital to grow faster than your current revenue allows. This is where you enter the world of fundraising and investment.</p>

        <h3>What This Stage Looks Like</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>You have proven product-market fit</li>
          <li>You need capital to scale operations</li>
          <li>You're considering different funding options</li>
          <li>You're preparing pitch decks and financial models</li>
          <li>You're networking with potential investors</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Key Challenges</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Funding Strategy:</strong> Choosing the right type of funding</li>
          <li><strong>Valuation:</strong> Determining your company's worth</li>
          <li><strong>Investor Relations:</strong> Building relationships with investors</li>
          <li><strong>Due Diligence:</strong> Preparing for investor scrutiny</li>
          <li><strong>Growth Planning:</strong> Using capital effectively</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>What You Need to Know</h3>
        <p>Fundraising is a full-time job that can take 6-12 months. You need to be prepared for rejection, have a clear growth plan, and understand the trade-offs of taking external capital.</p>

        <h3>Funding Options</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Bootstrapping:</strong> Growing with existing revenue</li>
          <li><strong>Friends & Family:</strong> Early-stage personal connections</li>
          <li><strong>Angel Investors:</strong> Individual high-net-worth investors</li>
          <li><strong>Venture Capital:</strong> Institutional investment funds</li>
          <li><strong>Debt Financing:</strong> Loans and credit lines</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Critical Preparation</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Financial projections and models</li>
          <li>Market analysis and competitive positioning</li>
          <li>Team and organizational structure</li>
          <li>Growth strategy and milestones</li>
          <li>Risk assessment and mitigation plans</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Next Steps</h3>
        <p>When you secure funding and are ready to scale operations, you're entering the "Ready to Expand" stage. This is where you use capital to accelerate growth.</p>

        <div class="bg-indigo-50 dark:bg-indigo-900/20 p-6 rounded-lg border-l-4 border-indigo-500">
          <h4>ðŸ’¼ Pro Tip</h4>
          <p>Choose investors who bring more than money. Look for strategic value, industry expertise, and networks that can help your business grow beyond just capital.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </Content>

  <CallToAction
    id="funding-cta"
    class="py-16 md:py-24"
    background="dark"
    title="Ready to Scale Operations?"
    subtitle="Get guidance for using capital to accelerate growth."
    actions={[
      { text: 'Ready to Expand', href: '/article/ready-to-expand', variant: 'primary' },
      { text: 'Browse All Articles', href: '/article' },
    ]}
  />
</Layout>
